Mobile District celebrates Black History Month

Sonya Rodgers, Chief of the Office of Small Business Programs, speaks at the Black History Month Luncheon, February 1, 2022, Mobile, Alabama. As well as being Chief of Small Business Programs, Rodgers has also served as the EEO Black Employment Manager for the past 25 years.

Joe Womack, retired U.S. Marine Corps Major, president of the Clean, Healthy Educated, Safe & Sustainable Community, Inc., and co-founder of the Africatown Heritage Preservation Foundation, speaks at the Mobile Distirct’s Black History Month Luncheon, February 1, 2023, in Mobile, Alabama.

Catherine Cummings, Chief of Equal Employment Opportunity Office, was named the 2022 USACE Diversity and Inclusion EEO Professional of the Year. Cummings has been the EEO Chief of the Mobile District since 2008.

Vongmony Var, U.S. Army Corps of Engineers, Mobile District Chief of the Economics Team, speaks during the Asian American/Pacific Islander Heritage Month luncheon at the District Headquarters, Mobile, Alabama, May 21, 2024. The AAPI luncheon provided an opportunity for those of AAPI descent to share their experiences and offer employees the opportunity to learn about AAPI culture. (U.S. Army photo by Jeremy Murray)
Happy Pride Month

Marco Mays, Director of Programs for Montgomery Pride in Montgomery, AL, delivers an inspiring and insightful presentation to district employees at the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers, Mobile District's Pride Month celebration on June 25, 2024.

Hai Le, U.S. Army Corps of Engineers, Mobile District Chief of the Data Management Section, speaks during the Asian American/Pacific Islander Heritage Month luncheon at the District Headquarters, Mobile, Alabama, May 21, 2024. The U. S. chose May as AAPI Heritage Month because it commemorates the first Japanese immigrant from May 7, 1843, and the completion of the transcontinental railroad on May 10, 1869, which was constructed with the labor of approximately 20,000 Chinese migrants. (U.S. Army photo by Jeremy Murray)

Marco Mays, Director of Programs for Montgomery Pride in Montgomery, AL, receives a certificate of appreciation from Kris Mullins, Chief of Staff of the Mobile District, U.S. Army Corps of Engineers, on June 25, 2024. The presentation took place during the District's Pride Month Celebration, where Mays was recognized for his insightful and inspiring talk to the attendees.
